  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. For each breed, compute the fraction of cats with dark fur: Tabby 4/15 &asymp; 0.267; Persian 5/14 &asymp; 0.357; Maine Coon 8/22 &asymp; 0.364; Siamese 6/18 = 1/3 &asymp; 0.333. The fraction 1/3 is exactly 0.333, so the Siamese breed has a dark-fur fraction equal to (and therefore closest to) 1/3. Choices A, B, and C are incorrect because their dark-fur fractions (0.267, 0.357, and 0.364) are farther from 1/3 than the Siamese fraction is.</p>",
